---
description: "Automatically use the verifier subagent after meaningful code changes"
alwaysApply: true
---

Use the Cursor verifier subagent proactively after meaningful code changes.

The verifier should confirm that:

- the Grill Gate was completed or explicitly skipped
- the Goal Contract was approved before planning
- the detailed Technical Implementation Plan was approved before editing
- the approved goal was reached
- every acceptance criterion is satisfied
- non-goals were respected
- approved interfaces, data shapes, and flows match the implementation
- pitfalls and regression risks from the plan were addressed
- configured checks meaningfully support the approved goal
- loop guardrails were respected when repeated iterations were used
- the Changeset Review Loop ran before human review
- no `CRITICAL` changeset review findings remain, or the work is marked blocked

If the subagent is unavailable, use the portable verifier skill from `.agents/skills/verifier/SKILL.md`.
